    "Andreina et al.",
    "(2021) integrates a feedback loop to detect these attacks by having randomly selected clients validate the global model each round.",
    "In BaFFLe, detection is based on analyzing per-class error rates, with unusual misclassifications indicating potential backdoor activity.",
    "Additionally, the Local Outlier Factor (LOF) method is used to identify model outliers across rounds, flagging backdoor attacks.",
    "BaFFLe reduces its ability to detect early-stage backdoor attacks, and it focuses primarily on backdoor detection, with plans to expand defenses against other poisoning attacks in future work."
